<p id="test_id">This line contains html tags, so don&#39;t touch it</p>

<ol>
<li>
<a href="/download/">Download</a> Pagegen and unpack to a directory
</li>
<li>
Ensure all files in the unpacked <strong>bin</strong> directory are executable (e.g. <tt>chmod 777 [unpacked dir]/bin/*</tt>)
</li>
<li>
Edit <strong>[unpacked directory]/bin/pagegen.conf</strong> and set the <strong>PAGEGENDIR</strong> variable to <strong>[unpacked directory]/bin</strong>
</li>
<li>
Create a directory to contain your site in the directory where you unpacked Pagegen (e.g. <tt>mkdir [unpacked dir]/my_site</tt>)
</li>
<li>
Run <tt>[unpacked directory]/bin/mksite my_site</tt> to generate the required files and directories
</li>
</ol>
